                "acceptedAnswer": { "@type": "Answer", "text": "No. There is no direct statutory conversion route from sole proprietorship to LLP under Indian law. The Limited Liability Partnership Act 2008 provides explicit conversion procedures only for partnership firms (Section 55), private companies (Section 56) and unlisted public companies (Section 57). The practical mechanism for a proprietor is to incorporate a fresh LLP via FiLLiP and then transfer the business via a Business Transfer Agreement, ideally structured as a slump sale under Section 50B of the Income Tax Act 1961." }
