            },
            {
                "@type": "Question",
                "name": "What are the tax implications of converting proprietorship to LLP?",
                "acceptedAnswer": { "@type": "Answer", "text": "Unlike proprietorship-to-company (which enjoys Section 47(xiv) tax-neutrality under conditions), there is no equivalent exemption for proprietorship-to-LLP. The transfer is taxable under Section 45 of the Income Tax Act 1961. Structured as a slump sale under Section 50B, capital gains are computed at the undertaking level (sale consideration minus net worth per Rule 11UAE) and CA-certified on Form 3CEA. Long-term capital gains rate applies if the business has been held for more than 36 months." }
