<!-- SECTION 15A: LEGAL FRAMEWORK -->
<section class="content-section">
    <div class="content-container">
        <div class="text-content">
            <h2 class="section-title">Legal and Compliance Framework</h2>
            <div class="content-text">
                
                <p><strong>LLP Governing Statute:</strong> Limited Liability Partnership Act 2008.</p>
                <p><strong>LLP Procedural Rules:</strong> Limited Liability Partnership Rules 2009.</p>
                <p><strong>Regulatory Status of Proprietorship-to-LLP:</strong> No direct statutory conversion route under LLP Act 2008 - only firm-to-LLP per Section 55, private company-to-LLP per Section 56 and unlisted public company-to-LLP per Section 57.</p>
                <p><strong>Practical Mechanism:</strong> Fresh LLP incorporation under LLP Act 2008 plus Business Transfer Agreement transferring the proprietorship business; the BTA is structured as a slump sale under Section 50B Income Tax Act where eligible.</p>
                <p><strong>LLP Minimum Requirements:</strong> Minimum 2 designated partners (at least 1 Indian resident under Section 7); no minimum capital contribution; registered office in India; LLP Agreement filed within 30 days of incorporation.</p>
                <p><strong>Indian Statute - Capital Gains:</strong> Income Tax Act 1961 - Section 45 (charging section); Section 50B (slump sale special computation); Section 2(42C) (definition of slump sale); Rule 11UAE Income Tax Rules (net worth computation methodology).</p>
                <p><strong>Section 47(xiv) Income Tax Act:</strong> Tax-neutrality for proprietorship-to-COMPANY conversion only (assets and liabilities transferred entirely; proprietor holds 50% shareholding for 5 years; no consideration other than shares); does NOT apply to proprietorship-to-LLP.</p>
                <p><strong>CA Report Requirement:</strong> Form 3CEA - CA-certified report mandatory for slump sale under Section 50B(3).</p>
                <p><strong>GST Statute - Going Concern:</strong> Central Goods and Services Tax Act 2017 - Notification 12/2017-Central Tax (Rate) provides nil GST rate on services by way of transfer of a going concern, as a whole or independent part thereof.</p>
                <p><strong>GST ITC Transfer:</strong> Rule 41 Central Goods and Services Tax Rules 2017 - transfer of unutilised Input Tax Credit via Form GST ITC-02 on transfer of business as a going concern.</p>
                <p><strong>GST Re-registration / Cancellation:</strong> Section 22 to 24 CGST Act 2017 (new LLP GSTIN under Form GST REG-01); Section 29 read with Rule 20 CGST Rules 2017 (cancellation of proprietorship GSTIN under Form GST REG-16).</p>
                <p><strong>Stamp Duty - LLP Agreement:</strong> Indian Stamp Act 1899 read with Delhi Stamp Schedule - INR 1,000 fixed plus contribution-linked stamp duty on the LLP Agreement.</p>
                <p><strong>Stamp Duty - Business Transfer Agreement:</strong> Indian Stamp Act 1899 read with Delhi Stamp Schedule - depends on whether the BTA includes immovable property (conveyance duty applies) or is purely movable (relatively lower stamp duty).</p>
                <p><strong>Forms - MCA21 v3:</strong> FiLLiP (incorporation); RUN-LLP module integrated within FiLLiP (name reservation); Form 9 (consent of designated partners, embedded in FiLLiP); Form 3 (LLP Agreement filing); Form 4 (partner change notice).</p>
                <p><strong>Forms - GSTN:</strong> Form GST REG-01 (new LLP GSTIN application); Form GST ITC-02 (ITC transfer on going concern); Form GST REG-16 (cancellation of proprietorship GSTIN).</p>
                <p><strong>Forms - Income Tax:</strong> Form 3CEA (slump sale CA report); ITR-3 / ITR-4 for proprietor for the final part-year period; ITR-5 for LLP from its incorporation date.</p>
                <p><strong>LLP Annual Compliance:</strong> Form 11 (Annual Return) within 60 days of FY end (30 May); Form 8 (Statement of Account and Solvency) within 30 days from end of 6 months from FY end (30 October); LLP audit if turnover above INR 40 lakh or contribution above INR 25 lakh; ITR-5 by 31 October following the FY end (or 31 July if audit not required).</p>
                <p><strong>Authority - LLP:</strong> Registrar of Companies (ROC), NCT of Delhi and Haryana, CGO Complex, Lodhi Road, New Delhi 110003; Central Registration Centre (CRC) for FiLLiP initial scrutiny.</p>
                <p><strong>Authority for source verification:</strong> MCA21 v3 at <a href="https://www.mca.gov.in" target="_blank" rel="noopener">mca.gov.in</a>, CBDT at <a href="https://www.incometaxindia.gov.in" target="_blank" rel="noopener">incometaxindia.gov.in</a>, CBIC GST at <a href="https://cbic-gst.gov.in" target="_blank" rel="noopener">cbic-gst.gov.in</a> and India Code (statutes) at <a href="https://www.indiacode.nic.in" target="_blank" rel="noopener">indiacode.nic.in</a>.</p>

            </div>
        </div>
    </div>
</section>

